The paper deals with interference cancellation in wireless networks, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of full duplex technology is a key aspect of the proposed scheme, which falls under the category of system design (cs.SY). The paper also discusses optimization algorithms for maximizing the downlink sum rate, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and communication (cs.COM) systems.
